# Monorepo

- Work inside a single top-level project: `cd <project-name>` before edits or package commands.
- Read that project’s `package.json` for scripts; there is no repo-root build or test.
- Match each project’s existing stack (React/Vite, plain HTML/JS, Maven, Python, etc.). Do not introduce new frameworks without an explicit user request.
- Conventions and project catalog: [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) and [`.claude/rules.md`](../../.claude/rules.md).

## Boundaries

- Do not commit paths under `crew-orbit/` (local Crew Orbit metadata; already in `.gitignore`).
- Run tests, installs, builds, or dev servers only when the user asks — not as automatic “verification” after edits.
